<p>For mice the equation is modified slightly to account for the difference in lifespan of the two species. To allow the ALiGeT window to have an approximately equal width across a given proportion of the mouse’s, we scaled the term 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="inf39">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mo>|</mo>
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>A</mi>
       <mi>g</mi>
      </msub>
      <mo>−</mo>
      <mi>T</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mo>|</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> by 650/78 where 650 days represents old age for a mouse and 78 represents old age for a human. A mouse genes ALiGeT score for a given age can thus be calculated as:
 <disp-formula id="equ2">
  <math id="m2">
   <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>S</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>g</mi>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mi>T</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msup>
      <mn>1.5</mn>
      <mrow>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <mfrac>
        <mrow>
         <mrow>
          <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
         </mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>A</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi>g</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mi>T</mi>
         <mrow>
          <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mo>(</mo>
         <mfrac>
          <mn>650</mn>
          <mn>78</mn>
         </mfrac>
         <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
       </mfrac>
      </mrow>
     </msup>
     <mo>∗</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
     <mi>E</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mstyle>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
